From these instances it seems to be abundantly obvious that in diplomatic, language the term Bag-man properly imports an in- denture or other legal deed executed under the seals of the parties ; and consequently that its application to the Rolls here in question implies that they are the record of the separate ragmans, or sealed in-

struments of homage and fealty, executed by the people of Scotland.
